{% block examples %}
### Basic example
Use the `Radio:Group`, `Radio:Field`, `Radio`, and `Label` components to create a simple radio group:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Basic example', {height: '200px'}) }}
We recommend adding an `aria-label` for assistive technology, or connecting the `Radio:Group` to your own label using `aria-labelledby`.

### With description
Use the `Radio:Field`, `Label`, and `Description` components to add a description below the radio:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With description', {height: '300px'}) }}

### With accent color
Use the `color` prop to choose a different accent color for a checkbox:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With accent color', {height: '200px'}) }}

### Default selected state
Use the `defaultValue` prop to set the default selected option for a `Radio:Group`:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Default selected state', {height: '200px'}) }}

### With fieldset
Use the `Fieldset`, `Legend`, and `Text` components to add a title and description to a radio group:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'With fieldset', {height: '350px'}) }}
When used with a `Fieldset` and `Legend`, you don't need to add a separate `aria-label` to the `Radio:Group` itself.

### Disabled state
Add the `disabled` prop to a `Radio` or `Radio:Field` component to disable it:
{{ toolkit_code_example(kit_id.value, component.name, 'Disabled state', {height: '350px'}) }}
You can also add the `disabled` prop to a `Radio:Group` or `Fieldset` to disable all of the radio buttons in that group.
